This is a template to generate links to entries for individual pinball titles at the Internet Pinball Database]. It should only be used in the "external links" section of an article. 

== Usage ==
The '''required''' parameter is the ID number. The template then uses the article title as the [[锚文本|anchor text]]:
<pre>
* {{IPDB | ID }}
* {{IPDB | 2 = ID }}
</pre>
To have the link text be other than the article name, use second parameter:
<pre>
* {{IPDB | ID | Name }}
* {{IPDB | id = ID | title = Title }}
</pre>

== Instructions ==
# Go to {{URL|https://www.ipdb.org/}} and find the link for the appropriate game
# Follow the link to go to the game's page. 
# The URL will look like this: <code><nowiki>https://www.ipdb.org/machine.cgi?id=<!-- ID --></nowiki></code>. Copy the part of the url which is substituted here with <nowiki><!-- ID --></nowiki>. This will be the first parameter (or <code>id=</code>).
# Add the game's name in the next parameter (or <code>name=</code>) if it is different from the page name.
# Add one of the following to the external links section of the article:
: <nowiki>* {{IPDB | id= <<!-- ID --> }}</nowiki>
: <nowiki>* {{IPDB | <!-- ID --> }}</nowiki>
: <nowiki>* {{IPDB | id= <!-- ID --> | title= <!-- title --> }}</nowiki>
: <nowiki>* {{IPDB | <!-- ID --> | <!-- title --> }}</nowiki>

